12-10-29":0.998,"2012-10-30":0.996,"2012-10-31":0.924,"2012-11-01":0.653,"2012-11-02":0.608,"2012-11-03":0.447,"2012-11-04":0.296,"2012-11-05":0.406,"2012-11-06":0.429,"2012-11-07":0.967,"2012-11-08":0.991}}],"blooms":[{"date":"2012-10-29","x":762.5,"y":268.2,"label":"New Jersey & New York: 145 recorded events · 113 deaths · $25.0B"}],"beats":[{"date":"2012-10-08","line":"The ground is quiet. But the Arctic Oscillation already reads -0.48 — out over the Atlantic a block is setting up before anyone on the coast has felt a thing."},{"date":"2012-10-23","line":"The block hardens. The Arctic Oscillation settles to -2.46 and holds — a wall of high pressure over the North Atlantic with nowhere for a storm to escape but west."},{"date":"2012-10-26","line":"Offshore, the barometer starts to fall. Buoy 44025 reads 1019.6 mb and dropping — the low is finding its footing over open water."},{"date":"2012-10-28","line":"The fall keeps steepening. By Oct 28 buoy 44025 is down to 1001.5 mb, and the track bends hard toward the coast the block walled off."},{"date":"2012-10-29","line":"The barometer bottoms at 958.2 mb offshore and the water comes for the harbor. The Battery crests 9.15 feet above the tide it was owed — higher than any day it has on record; up the Sound Kings Point tops 12.57 feet, Long Island funneling a bad tide into a record one."},{"date":"2012-10-30","line":"Then the ground answers. New Jersey & New York: 145 recorded storm events, 113 deaths, $25 billion in losses on the books — the water the offshore low foretold."},{"date":"2012-10-31","line":"The block finally lets go and the storm's remains spin inland. But the bill on the ground has already come due."},{"date":"2012-11-08","line":"The archive kept every thread of it: the block, the offshore low, the harbor gauges that all rose on the same day. Nobody had to draw the lines — the readings did."}]}